<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aluminum Co. of America: The Pittsburgh, Pa., firm known as Alcoa reported a 
second-quarter profit of $161.9 million, down from $285.2 million for the same 
period in 1989. Sales for the 1990 quarter were $2.69 billion, down from $2.76 
billion in 1989. Earnings reflected a 24% drop in aluminum ingot prices, lower 
fabricated product activity and a large decrease in revenue from the company's 
Brazilian affiliate as a result of that government's economic policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
