<TEXT>
<P>
W. R. Grace &amp; Co.: The New York-based chemical company said second-quarter 
profit totaled $51.3 million, up 16% from the same period a year ago. Sales 
rose 8% to $1.6 billion. The largest operating unit of the company, Grace 
Specialty Chemicals Co., posted a 10% after-tax gain in operating income, 
helped by advances in its packaging operations business and higher sales of 
high-speed drying equipment used by the printing industry. 
</P>
