<TEXT>
<P>
Bernstein Bows Out of Tour: Conductor Leonard Bernstein has canceled several 
performances in Japan due to exhaustion and lingering illness, and was escorted 
back to New York Monday by his physician, Dr. Kevin Cahill. "Leonard Bernstein 
is suffering from exhaustion as a result of trying to fulfill his professional 
obligations while not having fully recovered from several ailments he suffered 
this spring," including severe influenza, pleurisy and pneumonia, said Cahill, 
who has ordered the 71-year-old conductor to rest "for an extended period." 
Bernstein had been scheduled to conduct the London Symphony Orchestra in four 
performances in Japan. GREG BRAXTON 
</P>
