Rare Elvis on Film: A collection of never-before-seen photographs of Elvis 
Presley on tour in 1956 will be the focus of "Elvis Close-Up: Jay Leviton 
Photographs" at the New Orleans Museum of Art from Aug. 3 to Oct. 4. The 
exhibition features 120 photos of Presley that Leviton took for Collier's 
magazine, which ceased publication before the photos could be published. Scenes 
include Presley relaxing backstage between performances, eating in diners, and 
on the verge of collapse from exhaustion. GREG BRAXTON 
