<TEXT>
<P>
Stick Up for Your Rights: Virgin Records will begin implementing its own brand 
of warning label for rock records starting in August -- a pro-First Amendment 
sticker. Jeff Ayeroff, Virgin's co-managing director, told The Times Monday 
that all Virgin Records albums, tapes and CDs will feature an anti-censorship 
label that reads: "The First Amendment gives you the right to choose what you 
hear, what you say and what you think. 
</P>
<P>
CENSORSHIP IS UNAMERICAN. Don't let anyone take away that right. Raise your 
political voice. Register to vote." Ayeroff said that Virgin will also make the 
label available to artists at other companies. Boogie Down Productions, a rap 
group that records for RCA, is slated to be the first outside artist to use the 
new sticker, he said. GREG BRAXTON 
