Left-hander Mark Langston held Milwaukee to just three runs but the Angels 
couldn't provide much offense and his record fell to 4-11. ROBERT LACHMAN / Los 
Angeles Times; Photo, Lee Stevens, brought up from Edmonton to replace injured 
Wally Joyner at first base for the Angels, makes a tag on Milwaukee's Dave 
Parker. PETER ROSS / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
