<DATE>
<P>
July 17, 1990, Tuesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 14; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
83 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
George Steinbrenner sent the bulk of his evidence to Fay Vincent's lawyers, 
starting the timetable for the baseball commissioner's decision in the 
four-month investigation of the owner of the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
Vincent is investigating the relationship between Steinbrenner, former Yankee 
outfielder Dave Winfield and Howie Spira, a New Yorker who received $40,000 in 
checks from Steinbrenner. 
</P>
<P>
Stephen E. Kaufman, Steinbrenner's attorney, would not say what type of 
evidence was submitted. 
</P>
