<HEADLINE>
<P>
SUSPECT HELD IN HOLDUP OF CABBIE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BLAKE FONTENAY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Police have arrested a man who they believe attacked and robbed a cabdriver 
Friday night, but the person who killed another cabdriver Saturday night is 
still at large, a police spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles police arrested Lester McGibbon, 33, of Plattsburg, N.Y., in 
connection with the armed robbery of a Yellow Cab Co. driver Saturday morning, 
San Diego Police Department spokesman Bill Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Police found McGibbon lying injured near a Yellow Cab at the intersection of 
Brannick Avenue and Hammel Street in Los Angeles about 9:30 a.m. Saturday, 
Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
McGibbon told police that he had been beaten and robbed by several people 
carrying clubs and sticks, and he was taken to a local hospital, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
"The doctor there said that his femur was fractured because he had been shot in 
the leg," Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
In the incident Friday night, driver William Joseph Tufford struggled with a 
gun-wielding attacker before the man stole his cab and escaped. McGibbon may 
have shot himself during that struggle, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
A license plate check on the cab found in Los Angeles showed that it had been 
stolen from San Diego, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Police are still looking for a suspect in the murder of Leonard Brumlow, 
another Yellow Cab driver who was shot and killed Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
McGibbon was in police custody at the time of Brumlow's death, Robinson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
