FCC Seeking to Cut Overseas Phone Rates: The Federal Communications Commission 
is seeking to force down international phone rates by 50% within three years, 
an action that could save American consumers billions of dollars a year, the 
New York Times reported. The agency contends that foreign telephone monopolies 
are keeping rates artificially high, despite cost-saving improvements in 
technology, the Times said. The FCC effort is likely to meet stiff resistance 
from foreign governments. 
