<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: NEW LOCKHEED COMPANY TO MODIFY BOEING 747S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lockheed Corp. established a new subsidiary, Lockheed Commercial Aircraft 
Center Inc., to maintain and modify Boeing 747 commercial jumbo jets beginning 
in mid-December. 
</P>
<P>
The Calabasas-based aerospace and defense concern said the new unit will have 
headquarters in San Bernardino, and its president will be Gary Bowring, a 
30-year veteran of the commercial aircraft maintenance industry. 
</P>
<P>
Lockheed previously had announced plans for its commercial aircraft group to 
occupy two bays of a four-bay hangar at Norton Air Force Base near San 
Bernardino, and to occupy the whole hangar when the Air Force closes the base 
in 1994. 
</P>
</TEXT>
