<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROCKWELL TO MOVE ITS HEADQUARTERS TO ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DEAN TAKAHASHI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEAL BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockwell International Corp. announced plans Monday to move its corporate 
headquarters from a leased building in El Segundo to a company-owned facility 
here. 
</P>
<P>
The move will make Rockwell, a diversified defense, electronics and aerospace 
firm with annual revenues of more than $12.5 billion, by far the largest public 
company based in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
"We are making this move from leased office space to provide an improved, more 
efficient working environment in company-owned facilities for our employees," 
said Donald R. Beall, Rockwell's chairman and chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
The relocation, which affects only about 235 employees, is slated to be 
completed in January, 1992, spokesman Jeff Charney said. 
</P>
<P>
It will also make Beall's daily commute a little easier. He lives in Newport 
Beach and typically flies from John Wayne Airport to El Segundo by helicopter. 
Rockwell officials said the move is not related to Beall's commute. Rather, 
Charney said, the headquarters is being moved because it will be a better use 
of corporate assets to occupy a building already owned by Rockwell instead of 
leasing space. 
</P>
<P>
The 250,000-square-foot, eight-story building is partially occupied by the 
company's information-systems unit. To make room for the headquarters staff, 
some of the 594 employees in the information-systems unit will be moved 
elsewhere within the complex, spokesman Fred Evans said. 
</P>
<P>
The new headquarters will be lodged in a 23-year-old building within a 100-acre 
complex owned by Rockwell in Seal Beach, where the company already has a large 
presence with its Strategic Defense Center and its Satellite &amp; Space 
Electronics division. 
</P>
<P>
Rockwell, which has 109,000 employees worldwide, is the second-largest employer 
in Orange County with 10,800 workers here. Only Hughes Aircraft Co. has more 
workers in the county. Rockwell will surpass Irvine-based Fluor Corp., which 
has annual sales of $6.3 billion, as the largest public company based here. 
</P>
<P>
Rockwell's operations scattered throughout the county reflect the corporation's 
diverse range of businesses. The company makes everything from guidance systems 
for the MX missile in Anaheim to communications satellites in Seal Beach. 
</P>
<P>
The operations include the defense electronics group in Anaheim, which employs 
6,300 people; the satellite and space electronics unit in Seal Beach with 1,181 
people, and a semiconductor manufacturing group in Newport Beach with 1,335. 
The rest of the company's employees in the county are scattered throughout 
other sites in Cypress, Seal Beach, Anaheim, Newport Beach and Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
Lucien Truhill, president and chief executive of the Orange County Chamber of 
Commerce, welcomed Rockwell's move. 
</P>
<P>
"While the numbers of employees are small, it is a significant corporate 
headquarters relocation," Truhill said. 
</P>
<P>
He noted that the county has lost several corporate headquarters in the past 
few years. The most noteworthy was when American Stores, a multibillion-dollar 
supermarket chain, moved its headquarters from Irvine to Salt Lake City in 
1988. 
</P>
<P>
While other defense companies are laying off workers, Rockwell has cushioned 
itself by reducing its dependence on defense revenues for several years. Last 
year, the company's defense electronics operation accounted for only 26.9% of 
revenue in fiscal 1989, contrasted with 49.7% in fiscal 1986. 
</P>
<P>
For the year ended Sept. 30, 1989, Rockwell reported net income of $734.9 
million on revenue of $12.5 billion, compared with net income of $811.9 million 
on revenue of $11.9 billion a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Rockwell has occupied the building in El Segundo since 1975, and the 
headquarters staff moved from Pittsburgh into that building in 1987. Beall said 
the company will keep its North American Aircraft unit, which has 3,800 
employees, in El Segundo. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
